HEADWORD: Octyl
<hw>Oc"tyl</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Oct</ets>ane +
<ets>-yl</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A hypothetical
hydrocarbon radical regarded as an essential residue of octane, and as
entering into its derivatives; <as>as, <ex>octyl</ex>
alcohol</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

